Fvwm is a powerful window manager.  Version 2.5.16 is a beta
release that fixes some build problems in the prior 2.5.15
release.  Please be aware that any features introduced in the
2.5.x development versions may be renamed, changed or removed
without notice before 2.6.0.

Upgrading from 2.5.15 is necessary if one of these problems was
encountered.  Otherwise, upgrading is optional.

This release is available at the home page: http://www.fvwm.org/.

New features:

   - If the pointer can not be grabbed in functions, a message is
     printed to the console instead of beeping.

* Bug Fixes:

   - Fixed a couple of build problems introduced in 2.5.15.
